storyInfo: Gitano finishes her lesson with the young Operators when she meets Croissant, who's coming to teach the next. Croissant seems to have run into some issues with her business, and after receiving compensation, Gitano divines Croissant's fortune for her.

attributes.content: Weekend
Rhodes Island Cafeteria
And so, just like that—
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: And your cards naturally fall like water from one hand—
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Into the other.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Wow!
attributes.name: Young Studying Operator

attributes.content: Do you know how?
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: I still don't!!
attributes.name: Young Studying Operator

attributes.content: Do it again, Gitano!
attributes.name: Young Studying Operator

attributes.content: *clears throat* Now, watch carefully.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Okay—
attributes.name: Young Studying Operator

attributes.content: Wow!
attributes.name: Young Studying Operator

attributes.content: Do you understand now?
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Nooope—
attributes.name: Young Studying Operator

attributes.content: Really?
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Regrettably, however, that's the end of today's cardistry lesson.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Awww—
attributes.name: Young Studying Operator

attributes.content: How about one more time?
attributes.name: Young Studying Operator

attributes.content: Then the person teaching here in a short while will be quite angry with me.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: You wouldn't want to see me get castigated, would you?
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Just one more, one little bit more? It'll be okay, right?
attributes.name: Young Studying Operator

attributes.content: Rules are very important. You cannot let your desires lead you to willingly abandon them.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Hmm—
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Such as it is, I'll give you all some homework.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: If anyone can show us the fruits of their practice by next week's lesson...
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Then—
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: You may draw one reward from the teacher's Treasure Chest.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: The Treasure Chest?
attributes.name: Young Studying Operator

attributes.content: Really?!
attributes.name: Young Studying Operator

attributes.content: Really and truly. Just two days ago, your teacher even added something quite fun to it.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: As long as you can summon the courage to give us all a display, everyone will get a share.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Yay!
attributes.name: Young Studying Operator

attributes.content: Alright, class dismissed. Don't forget, keep your cards and toys safe with you.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: We'll meet next week.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Bye, Miss!
attributes.name: Young Studying Operator

attributes.content: Phew...
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Phewie and a half. Breathe easy, miss. Lessons still runnin' slick?
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: You might get the impression they're lessons, but it's really just entertaining the children.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: You have the greater burden.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: It takes quite a lot of brainpower and effort, teaching children the rules of arithmetic.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Ain't no nightmare, really. Play numbers long 'nuff 'n they get it.
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: 'n what I teach ain't no mathematics. Umm, what was that name I picked it?
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: 'Business Fanatics Class?' Somethin' like that.
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: Aw, shucks, I'm just the same as you. Three cheers fer fun 'n none fer learnin'.
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: And that's quite good.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: After all, it's a very cruel thing, doing business.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: You get me, ma'am.
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: Though it was never originally intended as such, divination is also fundamentally a sort of business.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: So it goes.
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: I'll let you set up the classroom in peace, then. Farewell.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Hrmmm—
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: Hm?
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: Oh, right!
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: Gitano, one second, please!
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: Do you need anything?
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: It's like this, see. Doctor seems fixin' ta head out far with Gavial, makin' fer a corner of Sargon.
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: Mm-hm.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: And me, I'm gettin' ready to visit with, see if I can't do a li'l dealin' while I'm there.
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: Yes, I follow.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: So I thought, uh. Y'see, uh. If you could juuuuust do me a li'l favor, gimme a tellin'?
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: You ought to know—
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: I know there is, yep, just, urm, how do I break this—
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: Spent all my money on gettin' stock in, ha, and now I ain't got a red cent on me.
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: *Sigh*.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: I won't take any money as compensation.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Ya serious? That's mighty fine!
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: But I will need you to promise something.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: You must promise me this—
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: You will not sell anything to the children during class.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Not even if it's 'just snacks.'
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Uh, haha.
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: Aw, heck, what makes you think I'd do somethin' like that?
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: Class might be a circus, but I still teach 'em proper.
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: You might, you might not. Neither has any bearing on me.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: I simply need your promise, and that will be my price.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: 'n if I go back on it?
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: Who knows?
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Hm...
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: What do you think?
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Sold!
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: I have accepted your payment.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: No need fer a... contract or somesuch?
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: Hmm?
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Our agreement is built upon our trust in each other. We need no contract.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Huh.
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: In that case, let us begin.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Considering class is about to start, we'll employ a more simple divination method.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: (Pulls out tarot deck)
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Whoa, that's... some crafts, ain't it!
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: Feels like every card in there'd fetch big money.
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: Way you spread out 'n spin' 'em on the table, is that shufflin'?
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: Yes. Please wait a moment.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Could just shuffle 'em fancy in one shot, like you were teachin'.
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: Some diviners will do it like that, true.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: But it's too harmful to the cards.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Just like the voyager pushing stubbornly through a blizzard: no matter how healthy, or how warm the clothes, their warmth is pulled away trace by trace in the end.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: The moment warmth is lost, all remedy will be of avail no more.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Ahaha...
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: Just a comparison Sami tend to use fairly often. I imagine you comprehend it.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Yup, yup, I getcha.
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: All ready now?
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: Mm. They're ready. They should be able to shine a light for you on some of your conundrums.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Gather them together, cut them once, and starting from where you've cut them, lay down three cards.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Remember, do not turn them over yet.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: So ya don't actually do a darn thing, Gitano?
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: I'm merely your guide in understanding. Shouldn't you uncover your own fate?
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Or, perhaps, you're easily willing to lay your fate in others' hands?
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Alrght, I get it now. Lemme at 'em!
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: Stack 'em up... cut... lay three cards face down in front.
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: That oughta be good, right?
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: Your movements are very direct. It seems you are not adrift.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Darn tootin'.
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: Well, then. Please.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Turn a card however you wish.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Ya been so dead serious all this time. Got some pressure on me.
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: There's nothing to be scared of. Come.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Reveal your first card.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: (Flips card)
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: The Knight of Cups, Reversed.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Ya gotta fill me in. Does forward or backward matter anythin'?
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: To put it simply, reversed cards symbolize that you are currently hindered by something.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Huh?!
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: Relax. These hindrances are not necessarily bad in meaning.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: They simply mean that right now, you are unable to successfully proceed.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Breakthrough, and success, perhaps aren't too far away.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Gotcha.
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: Let me look carefully.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Have you run into any problems doing business?
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Uh, suppose I have.
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: That's how it goes more or less every month. Sometimes I blunder decidin', 'n then I don't earn nothin.' Pain in my keister.
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: You've probably seen an opportunity, but failed to grasp it.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: That's the story of anyone doin' business any day of the week.
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: So this time, you've prepared to stake it all?
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: I trust my intuition. Headin' to Gavial's ol' place is gonna pay off big!
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: I see.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: By my understanding, Rhodes Island's procurement services have always been short of hands. As long as you're willing to help them with some work, money won't be a problem, and most risk will be shouldered by Rhodes Island instead.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Why choose to go it alone?
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: That, huh.
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: Used to workin' by myself.
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: It seems your decisions are not wholly profit-seeking.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Ain't as grand as ya put it, neither. Just seein' the world fer myself, makin' some money on the side to patch up expenses.
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: Always gotta spend money fer the good stuff, after all.
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: I understand.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: So this, uh, this here card, basically, it ain't no good sign.
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: Coming events will not be smooth.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: So can I just—Gitano—ya gotta teach me!
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: Don't rush. This is merely a beginning.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Come. Reveal your second card.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: D'awwwgh, alright...
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: (Shakes as she flips a card)
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: The Ace of Wands, Upright.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Wh... what's this one mean...?
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: You have seized an opportunity, and are about to receive an advantage in life from it.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Though there may be great danger, you have issued your challenge to life with full conviction.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Sounds like a good thing.
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: When I divined for myself, I once came to this one too.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Whoa—y'all can even do divination fer yerselves?
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: When a flash of miraculous light strikes, diviners are utterly capable of peering into their own paths.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: 'n here I thought diviners only took money 'n did stuff fer other folk.
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: Ultimately, currency cannot settle all questions.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Moreover, there are some paths outsiders have no recourse to interfere in. Only by conversing with themselves, feeling through things, pursuing, can they grasp a chance at a clue.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Gets pretty darn complicated, then.
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: It's just like how you choose to conduct business by yourself, Croissant. All your decisions, any of your choices, they're all crystallizations of your years of business experience, aren't they?
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Others can only give suggestions. The power to decide lies eternally in your own hand—just as it does now.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Even if all three cards portended the worst outcome, would you really change your decisions?
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Money's spent...
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: So you've only come seeking a comfort of sorts, hoping I might give you reassuring results.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Ah—no need to answer me. Many are like that. I understand it very well.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: All of us will tend to hope for something unrealistic in uncertain times, something that'll resolve it all.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Unfortunately, I'm not what you've all been hoping for.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: All I can do is peer shallow into the road ahead, and offer all the help I can.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: You've paid my terms, and so I have a responsibility to spare no effort for you.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Only this, and nothing more.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Gitano...
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: Let us continue.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Al... Alrighty.
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: You will have an adventure, but it seems your journey won't be serene.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: As for the outcome, we may look to the last card to show our answer.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: I can't say whether there'll even be a single note of LMD at the end.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: It just keeps gettin' more dangerous...
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: I only bring up a poorer kind of possibility.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Returning with overflowing riches is not out of possibility's realm, either.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Gosh, could ya imagine?
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: I'll be visiting Perfumer's sometime for a complete course of aromatic sleep therapy, then.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: I'll leave the bill to you.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: I make some cash 'n I'll cover ya!
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: Hm-hmm. It's a done deal.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Now, then, let us explore your destination in this journey.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Your final card, please.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: (Flips tarot card with a swish)
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: The Moons, Upright.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: So it's upright. 'kay, good start.
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: This is... certainly hard to say.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Have... you ever looked into Gavial's hometown situation before?
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: I've surveyed Sargon markets before. This stuff'll sell like hotcakes!
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: If so, that'll be the best outcome.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: (Is there any possibility it won't be an ordinary Sargon market, I wonder...)
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: (The Moons upright...)
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Your journey will not be serene. The fore cards tell of that much.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Be wary of deception, and wary of being cheated.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: In my view, if possible, do proceed cautiously.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Do you like the moons?
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Like? Can't say I do fer sure? But when I'm moody out on the deck 'n look up 'n see the moons, that makes me feel alright some.
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: And the moonshadow?
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Umm. Do folk specifically go lookin' fer the shadow?
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: Under the radiance of the moon, things often come to be ignored.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: The things this card shows are also as such.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: There is always that which is hidden by radiance, painstakingly concealed.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Whether it is fortune or sorrow requires your own careful consideration.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Noted. I'll be watchin' out.
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: And this should be what these cards have shown.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: What these three cards together make known to you.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Croissant, your future will not be relaxed.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: At the least, accompanying the Doctor on this journey out, there will be many hindrances.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Do you have any such feeling of your own? For example, a vague unease or confusion in your heart.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Kinda a li'l bit...
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: But push past, 'n I should be able to get over it.
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: Do the, uh, cards say I'm gonna lose my investment?
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: Not at all. Besides, the tarot never speaks in certainties of futures.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: So, still a chance I'm saved.
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: If I can't hold out, I oughta last 'nother couple days knockin' on my savin's jar.
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: Here's hoping.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: As for divining, things would wrap up here.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Is there anything else you need me for?
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Hmm...
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: Gitano, you pull a card too!
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: Oh?
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Didn'tcha just say diviners can divine themselves too?
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: I wanna see how yer luck is.
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: But that requires me to prepare—
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: C'mon, lessee.
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: The tarot is not—
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Aw, potayto potahto, c'mon. Draw.
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: (Draws a card 'for' Gitano.)
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: Come on. Flip it.
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: Wait. Let me prepare a moment.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Phew.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: (Flips tarot card)
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Ten of Cups... Reversed...
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: This mean somethin' bad?
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: Then lemme just turn it round—
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: Stay your hand and do not touch the card!
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Oh, alright...
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: Sorry, Gitano.
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: No.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: That's not it.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: The card's position is in relation to the revealer.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: So this card.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Is Upright.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Hmm?
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: Ohh...
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: Right! Yer sittin' opposite me!!
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: So this card mean somethin' good, then?
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: In regards to my occupation and personal relations, it's not bad at all.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Then—
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: (Grabs Gitano's hand and rubs it a few times)
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: Eh?
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Lemme borrow a li'l bit of yer good luck, a'ight? This way I can pay ya back.
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: If you so insist...
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: As you wish, then...
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Hoooo boy, yer gonna let me pay you back sure as sweeeeeet heck.
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: Ah!
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: What's wrong?
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: I just thoughta somethin'!
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: If I'm borrowin' yer good luck, don't that mean the whole divination we just did don't count fer nothin' now?
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: Who knows?
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: So there ain't no rule like that, huh.
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: If you want another divination, you will have to make a payment to me again.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Uh, yup. Pass, then.
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: Hmm...
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: Lemme rub a few more times. That oughta be free, right?
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: Hm-hmm~
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: I'll give you a discount on this one. Free it is.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Aw, thanks!
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: Five minutes later...
Hi, Croissant!!
attributes.name: Young Studying Operator

attributes.content: It's nice to meet you too, Gitano!
attributes.name: Young Studying Operator

attributes.content: Oooh.
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: Good day, all.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: Well, then. I'll be leaving now.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: I pray the LMD you earn will be enough to cram Rhodes Island full.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: You got it.
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: Next time ya got stuff to buy, remember, you find me. I'll give ya some deep discounts!
attributes.name: Croissant

attributes.content: Fate is a thing of constant change. We'll talk details when the time is right.
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: (Waves and leaves)
attributes.name: Gitano

attributes.content: (I hope my fortune can truly be of help to you, Croissant.)
attributes.name: Gitano
